         <abstract>
            <p>Series are considered whose general term is a rational function multiplied by a fractional power. The summation of such series is reduced, via Laplace transformation techniques, to a problem of quadrature, which is then solved by Gaussian quadrature relative to Einstein and Fermi weight functions. A number of examples are worked out in detail.</p>
          </abstract>
